README.md
     1ŌåÆ# dotenv [![NPM version](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/dotenv.svg?style=flat-square)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/dotenv) [![downloads](https://img.shields.io/npm/dw/dotenv)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/dotenv)
     3ŌåÆ<img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/motdotla/dotenv/master/dotenv.svg" alt="dotenv" align="right" width="200" />
     4ŌåÆ
     5ŌåÆDotenv is a zero-dependency module that loads environment variables from a `.env` file into [`process.env`](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/process.html#process_process_env). Storing configuration in the environment separate from code is based on [The Twelve-Factor App](https://12factor.net/config) methodology.
     6ŌåÆ
     7ŌåÆ[Watch the tutorial](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YtkZR0NFd1g)
     8ŌåÆ
     9ŌåÆ&nbsp;
    10ŌåÆ
    11ŌåÆ## Usage
    13ŌåÆInstall it.
    14ŌåÆ
    15ŌåÆ```sh
    16ŌåÆnpm install dotenv --save
    17ŌåÆ```
    18ŌåÆ
    19ŌåÆCreate a `.env` file in the root of your project:
    20ŌåÆ
    21ŌåÆ```ini
    22ŌåÆ# .env
    23ŌåÆS3_BUCKET="YOURS3BUCKET"
    24ŌåÆSECRET_KEY="YOURSECRETKEYGOESHERE"
    25ŌåÆ```
    26ŌåÆ
      ŌåÆŌĆ”
    39ŌåÆ## Advanced
    41ŌåÆ<details><summary>ES6</summary><br>
    42ŌåÆ
    43ŌåÆImport with [ES6](#how-do-i-use-dotenv-with-import):
    44ŌåÆ
    45ŌåÆ```javascript
    46ŌåÆimport 'dotenv/config'
    47ŌåÆ```
    48ŌåÆ
    49ŌåÆES6 import if you need to set config options:
    50ŌåÆ
    51ŌåÆ```javascript
    52ŌåÆimport dotenv from 'dotenv'
    53ŌåÆdotenv.config({ path: '/custom/path/to/.env' })
    54ŌåÆ```
      ŌåÆŌĆ”
   319ŌåÆ## Agents
   321ŌåÆ<img src="https://dotenvx.com/assets/img/as2/9.jpg" height="400" alt="dotenvx-as2" align="right"/>
   322ŌåÆ
   323ŌåÆ> Software is changing, and dotenv must change with itŌĆöthat is why I built [agentic secret storage (AS2)](https://dotenvx.com/as2). Agents run code without humans at terminals, so plaintext `.env` files are the wrong primitive.
   324ŌåÆ>
   325ŌåÆ> AS2 is built for autonomous software: encrypted by default, zero console access, and cryptographyŌĆæfirst delivery that keeps operators out of the loop.
   326ŌåÆ>
   327ŌåÆ> It is backed by [Vestauth](https://github.com/vestauth/vestauth), the trusted, pioneering auth layer for agentsŌĆögiving each agent a cryptographic identity so requests are signed with private keys and verified with public keys. No shared secrets to leak.
   328ŌåÆ>
   329ŌåÆ> It's what I'm using now. - [motdotla](https://mot.la)
   330ŌåÆ
   331ŌåÆ### Quickstart
   333ŌåÆInstall vestauth and initialize your agent.
   334ŌåÆ
   335ŌåÆ```bash
   336ŌåÆnpm i -g vestauth
   337ŌåÆ
   338ŌåÆvestauth agent init
   339ŌåÆ```
   340ŌåÆ
   341ŌåÆYour agent `set`s secrets with a simple `curl` endpoint:
   342ŌåÆ
   343ŌåÆ```bash
   344ŌåÆvestauth agent curl -X POST https://as2.dotenvx.com/set -d '{"KEY":"value"}'
   345ŌåÆ```
   346ŌåÆ
      ŌåÆŌĆ”
   357ŌåÆ## FAQ
   359ŌåÆ<details><summary>Should I commit my `.env` file?</summary><br/>
   360ŌåÆ
   361ŌåÆNo.
   362ŌåÆ
   363ŌåÆUnless you encrypt it with [dotenvx](https://github.com/dotenvx/dotenvx). Then we recommend you do.
   364ŌåÆ
   365ŌåÆ</details>
   366ŌåÆ<details><summary>What about variable expansion?</summary><br/>
   367ŌåÆ
   368ŌåÆUse [dotenvx](https://github.com/dotenvx/dotenvx).
   369ŌåÆ
   370ŌåÆ</details>
   371ŌåÆ<details><summary>Should I have multiple `.env` files?</summary><br/>
   372ŌåÆ
      ŌåÆŌĆ”
   579ŌåÆ## Docs
   581ŌåÆDotenv exposes four functions:
   582ŌåÆ
   583ŌåÆ* `config`
   584ŌåÆ* `parse`
   585ŌåÆ* `populate`
   586ŌåÆ
   587ŌåÆ### Config
   589ŌåÆ`config` will read your `.env` file, parse the contents, assign it to
   590ŌåÆ[`process.env`](https://nodejs.org/docs/latest/api/process.html#process_process_env),
   591ŌåÆand return an Object with a `parsed` key containing the loaded content or an `error` key if it failed.
   592ŌåÆ
   593ŌåÆ```js
   594ŌåÆconst result = dotenv.config()
   595ŌåÆ
   596ŌåÆif (result.error) {
   597ŌåÆ  throw result.error
   598ŌåÆ}
   599ŌåÆ
   600ŌåÆconsole.log(result.parsed)
   601ŌåÆ```
   602ŌåÆ
      ŌåÆŌĆ”
   605ŌåÆ#### Options
   607ŌåÆ##### path
   609ŌåÆDefault: `path.resolve(process.cwd(), '.env')`
   610ŌåÆ
   611ŌåÆSpecify a custom path if your file containing environment variables is located elsewhere.
   612ŌåÆ
   613ŌåÆ```js
   614ŌåÆrequire('dotenv').config({ path: '/custom/path/to/.env' })
   615ŌåÆ```
   616ŌåÆ
   617ŌåÆBy default, `config` will look for a file called .env in the current working directory.
   618ŌåÆ
   619ŌåÆPass in multiple files as an array, and they will be parsed in order and combined with `process.env` (or `option.processEnv`, if set). The first value set for a variable will win, unless the `options.override` flag is set, in which case the last value set will win.  If a value already exists in `process.env` and the `options.override` flag is NOT set, no changes will be made to that value. 
   620ŌåÆ
   621ŌåÆ```js  
   622ŌåÆrequire('dotenv').config({ path: ['.env.local', '.env'] })
   623ŌåÆ```
   624ŌåÆ
   625ŌåÆ##### quiet
   627ŌåÆDefault: `false`
   628ŌåÆ
   629ŌåÆSuppress runtime logging message.
   630ŌåÆ
   631ŌåÆ```js
   632ŌåÆ// index.js
   633ŌåÆrequire('dotenv').config({ quiet: false }) // change to true to suppress
   634ŌåÆconsole.log(`Hello ${process.env.HELLO}`)
   635ŌåÆ```
   636ŌåÆ
   637ŌåÆ```ini
   638ŌåÆ# .env
   639ŌåÆHELLO=World
   640ŌåÆ```
      ŌåÆŌĆ”
   648ŌåÆ##### encoding
   650ŌåÆDefault: `utf8`
   651ŌåÆ
   652ŌåÆSpecify the encoding of your file containing environment variables.
   653ŌåÆ
   654ŌåÆ```js
   655ŌåÆrequire('dotenv').config({ encoding: 'latin1' })
   656ŌåÆ```
   657ŌåÆ
   658ŌåÆ##### debug
   660ŌåÆDefault: `false`
   661ŌåÆ
   662ŌåÆTurn on logging to help debug why certain keys or values are not being set as you expect.
   663ŌåÆ
   664ŌåÆ```js
   665ŌåÆrequire('dotenv').config({ debug: process.env.DEBUG })
   666ŌåÆ```
   667ŌåÆ
   668ŌåÆ##### override
   670ŌåÆDefault: `false`
   671ŌåÆ
   672ŌåÆOverride any environment variables that have already been set on your machine with values from your .env file(s). If multiple files have been provided in `option.path` the override will also be used as each file is combined with the next. Without `override` being set, the first value wins. With `override` set the last value wins. 
   673ŌåÆ
   674ŌåÆ```js
   675ŌåÆrequire('dotenv').config({ override: true })
   676ŌåÆ```
   677ŌåÆ
   678ŌåÆ##### processEnv
   680ŌåÆDefault: `process.env`
   681ŌåÆ
   682ŌåÆSpecify an object to write your environment variables to. Defaults to `process.env` environment variables.
   683ŌåÆ
   684ŌåÆ```js
   685ŌåÆconst myObject = {}
   686ŌåÆrequire('dotenv').config({ processEnv: myObject })
   687ŌåÆ
   688ŌåÆconsole.log(myObject) // values from .env
   689ŌåÆconsole.log(process.env) // this was not changed or written to
   690ŌåÆ```
   691ŌåÆ
   692ŌåÆ### Parse
   694ŌåÆThe engine which parses the contents of your file containing environment
   695ŌåÆvariables is available to use. It accepts a String or Buffer and will return
   696ŌåÆan Object with the parsed keys and values.
   697ŌåÆ
   698ŌåÆ```js
   699ŌåÆconst dotenv = require('dotenv')
   700ŌåÆconst buf = Buffer.from('BASIC=basic')
   701ŌåÆconst config = dotenv.parse(buf) // will return an object
   702ŌåÆconsole.log(typeof config, config) // object { BASIC : 'basic' }
   703ŌåÆ```
   704ŌåÆ
   705ŌåÆ#### Options
   707ŌåÆ##### debug
   709ŌåÆDefault: `false`
   710ŌåÆ
   711ŌåÆTurn on logging to help debug why certain keys or values are not being set as you expect.
   712ŌåÆ
   713ŌåÆ```js
   714ŌåÆconst dotenv = require('dotenv')
   715ŌåÆconst buf = Buffer.from('hello world')
   716ŌåÆconst opt = { debug: true }
   717ŌåÆconst config = dotenv.parse(buf, opt)
   718ŌåÆ// expect a debug message because the buffer is not in KEY=VAL form
   719ŌåÆ```
   720ŌåÆ
   721ŌåÆ### Populate
   723ŌåÆThe engine which populates the contents of your .env file to `process.env` is available for use. It accepts a target, a source, and options. This is useful for power users who want to supply their own objects.
   724ŌåÆ
   725ŌåÆFor example, customizing the source:
   726ŌåÆ
   727ŌåÆ```js
   728ŌåÆconst dotenv = require('dotenv')
   729ŌåÆconst parsed = { HELLO: 'world' }
   730ŌåÆ
   731ŌåÆdotenv.populate(process.env, parsed)
   732ŌåÆ
   733ŌåÆconsole.log(process.env.HELLO) // world
   734ŌåÆ```
   735ŌåÆ
   736ŌåÆFor example, customizing the source AND target:
      ŌåÆŌĆ”
   748ŌåÆ#### options
   750ŌåÆ##### Debug
   752ŌåÆDefault: `false`
   753ŌåÆ
   754ŌåÆTurn on logging to help debug why certain keys or values are not being populated as you expect.
   755ŌåÆ
   756ŌåÆ##### override
   758ŌåÆDefault: `false`
   759ŌåÆ
   760ŌåÆOverride any environment variables that have already been set.
   761ŌåÆ
   762ŌåÆ&nbsp;
   763ŌåÆ
   764ŌåÆ## CHANGELOG
   766ŌåÆSee [CHANGELOG.md](CHANGELOG.md)
   767ŌåÆ
   768ŌåÆ&nbsp;
   769ŌåÆ
   770ŌåÆ## Who's using dotenv?
   772ŌåÆ[These npm modules depend on it.](https://www.npmjs.com/browse/depended/dotenv)
   773ŌåÆ
   774ŌåÆProjects that expand it often use the [keyword "dotenv" on npm](https://www.npmjs.com/search?q=keywords:dotenv).
